-- pd.package: FTD fira-code package
name: shaheen-senpai.github.io/fira-code

This FTD font `fira-code` package is for your ftd web projects. To Use this
fira-code inside `FTD` project follow below instructions.

-- ds.h3: How to use fira-code?

-- ds.code: Add this to your FASTN.ftd
lang: ftd

\-- fastn.dependency: shaheen-senpai.github.io/fira-code

-- ds.markdown: 

After adding fira-code dependency inside your `FASTN.ftd` file, You need to
add fira-code assets and import it inside your `.ftd` files where you are
using this font for your custom font types. 

To include fira-code into your `ftd` file follow below instructions.

-- ds.code:
lang: ftd

\-- import: shaheen-senpai.github.io/fira-code/assets as fira-code-assets


-- ds.h3: How to create a custom fira-code type? 

-- ds.markdown: 

We don't recommend creating custom types. We recommend to use 
our [fira-code-typography](https://shaheen-senpai.github.io/fira-code-typography)

If you're using [fira-code-typography](https://shaheen-senpai.github.io/fira-code-typography) 
and still your designer has introduced new font size which are not included or 
part of our [fira-code-typography](https://shaheen-senpai.github.io/fira-code-typography) 
then only define custom types. 

We hope you shouldn't need to define a custom type.

Below is an example of creating a custom `ftd.type` using fira-code.

-- ds.rendered:

-- ds.rendered.input:

\-- ftd.type fira-code-size-12-desktop:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $fira-code-assets.fonts.<font-name>


\-- ftd.type fira-code-size-12-mobile:
size.px: 12
weight: 400
font-family: $fira-code-assets.fonts.<font-name>

\-- ftd.responsive-type fira-code-size-12-400:
desktop: $fira-code-size-12-desktop
mobile: $fira-code-size-12-mobile

\-- ftd.text: 
role: $fira-code-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

üëâ The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog 

-- ds.rendered.output:

-- ftd.text: 
role: $fira-code-size-12-400
color: $inherited.colors.text-strong

`font-size: 12px, font-weight: 400` 

üëâ The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog 

